Asian wildcards Announced for Australian Open
CANBERRA , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- Japanese Takao Suzuki and South Korean Sung-Hee Park were named Thursday as the Asian wildcard entries to the 1999 Australian Tennis Open , according to reports from Sydney .
The Asian wildcard , introduced in 1997 , offers a maindraw berth to one man and one woman outside the entry cut-off but ranked within the top 200 and from a country not represented in the draw .
Tennis Australia President Geoff Pollard said : " The Asian wildcard has been an overwhelming success . "
The Australian Open starts in Melbourne on January 18 .
